title: Próchnowo, West Pomeranian Voivodeship
text:
Próchnowo is a <a href="village">village</a> in the administrative district of <a href="Gmina%20Miros%C5%82awiec">Gmina Mirosławiec</a>, within <a href="Wa%C5%82cz%20County">Wałcz County</a>, <a href="West%20Pomeranian%20Voivodeship">West Pomeranian Voivodeship</a>, in north-western Poland. It lies approximately east of <a href="Miros%C5%82awiec">Mirosławiec</a>, west of <a href="Wa%C5%82cz">Wałcz</a>, and east of the regional capital <a href="Szczecin">Szczecin</a>.
Before 1945 the area was part of <a href="Germany">Germany</a>. For the history of the region, see <a href="History%20of%20Pomerania">History of Pomerania</a>.
The village has a population of 210.
